/etc/linuxmuster/samba/root-postexec.d

Shell scripts placed in this directory will be executed by
/usr/sbin/samba-userlog via run-parts when user logs out of samba.

Variables which are available during runtime:
* USERNAME : login name of user logging out.
* REALNAME : real name of user logging out.
* PGROUP   : primary group of user logging out.
* HOMEDIR  : path to user's homedir.
* HOSTNAME : name of host from which user logs out.
* IP       : ip address of host from which user logs out.

